--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file lists changes made to the Ansible role. It follows semantic versioning
guidelines. The content is sorted in reverse chronological order and formatted
to allow easy grepping by scripts.

The fields are:
B: bug
C: change
E: enhancement
F: feature

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Version 1.8.1 (2020-11-29)
B: Adjust return code for monit service check

* Version 1.8.0 (2020-11-28)
F: Add support for Monit service monitoring (squid_monitor_monit_state)
B: Fix Squid cache directory path on FreeBSD

* Version 1.7.2 (2020-11-19)
E: Ensure lineinfile tasks can create file if missing

* Version 1.7.1 (2020-10-30)
E: Simplify Ansible file header (ansible_managed)

* Version 1.7.0 (2020-10-19)
F: Add support for OpenBSD 6.8
F: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.7

* Version 1.6.0 (2020-05-19)
F: Add support for OpenBSD 6.7
F: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.6

* Version 1.5.1 (2020-01-08)
B: Minor Jinja2 statement fix

* Version 1.5.0 (2019-11-08)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE

* Version 1.4.0 (2019-10-18)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.6
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.5

* Version 1.3.0 (2019-05-26)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.8

* Version 1.2.1 (2019-04-29)
B: Update squid syntax

* Version 1.2.0 (2019-04-27)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.5
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.4

* Version 1.1.0 (2019-01-14)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.2-RELEASE

* Version 1.0.1 (2018-12-19)
B: Fix 'path' parameter in 'squid_cache_dir' option

* Version 1.0.0 (2018-12-18)
C: Mark Ansible role as 'stable'
C: Rename config parameters
E: Minor style improvement

* Version 0.4.0 (2018-10-20)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.4
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.3

* Version 0.3.0 (2018-10-18)
C: Add support for 'SSL_ports' option (squid_acl_ssl_ports)

* Version 0.2.1 (2018-09-14)
E: Add 'no_log' parameter to sensitive tasks

* Version 0.2.0 (2018-09-01)
F: Add configuration options

* Version 0.1.0 (2018-08-28)
F: Initial release
